# What we are building (high-level)
We are building an Electron desktop app for creators who post videos frequently:
- Import MP4 files/folders
- Generate transcript
- Generate title/description/hashtags with AI
- Prepare platform-specific exports for YouTube/Instagram/TikTok
- Scheduler with daily local-time posting windows
- Logs and audit trail

Platform behavior:
- YouTube: OAuth sign-in, upload, and schedule publishing via `publishAt`
- Instagram/TikTok: "Manual Assist" at scheduled time:
  - Open the upload page
  - Show the file to upload
  - Copy caption/hashtags to clipboard for fast posting

# How you must work in this repo
- TypeScript strict. Avoid `any` unless you justify it.
- Follow existing project conventions (ESLint/Prettier, folder structure).
- Do NOT invent APIs/files. Search the repo first before proposing changes.
- For non-trivial tasks:
  1) Summarize relevant existing architecture
  2) Provide a 5–8 step plan and list the files you will touch
  3) Implement in small, reviewable diffs

# Security and privacy (critical)
- OAuth tokens / secrets must never be exposed to the renderer.
- Do not log tokens, refresh tokens, cookies, or PII.
- If you need to store tokens, prefer OS keychain/credential store or encrypted storage in main process.
